===Etymology 1===
An alteration of {{term|ballocks|lang=en}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|bollocks}} (''rarely used in the singular'')

# {{British|vulgar}} The [[testicle]]s (''sometimes used in the singular'')
# {{British|vulgar}} Nonsense or information deliberately intended to mislead.
#: ''That's a load of '''bollocks''', mate!''
# {{Ireland|vulgar}} An [[idiot]], an [[ignorant]] or disagreeable person.
#: ''Don't mind him; he's only an oul' '''bollocks'''!''
# {{British|vulgar}} A contraction of '''[[dog's bollocks|the dog's bollocks]]'''.

